OL,4,CHepatitis C tests spike after blood
OL,5,Cscandal news
OL,6,GThere has been a surge in demand for
OL,7,Ghepatitis C tests since the BBC
OL,8,Grevealed that hundreds of people in
OL,9,Gthe UK were unknowingly infected with
OL,10,Gthe virus, the Hepatitis C Trust says.
OL,12,FUp to 27,000 people caught it when
OL,13,Fthey were given transfusions with
OL,14,Finfected blood from the 1970s until
OL,15,F1991.
OL,17,FAccording to BBC analysis, a further
OL,18,F1,700 people who caught it in the same
OL,19,Fway have not yet been diagnosed.
OL,21,FLeft untreated, hepatitis can cause
OL,22,Fchronic liver disease and can be fatal.
